member.name: M:WindowsFormsApplication1.MMatrix.QRGramSchmidt
member.summary: Gram-Schmidtian orthogonalization of an m by n matrix A, such that {Q, R} is returned, where A = QR, Q is m by n and orthogonal, R is n by n and upper triangular matrix.

member.name: M:WindowsFormsApplication1.MMatrix.Eigenvalues
member.summary: Computes approximates of the eigenvalues of this matrix. WARNING: Computation uses basic QR iteration with Gram-Schmidtian orthogonalization. This implies that (1) only real matrices can be examined; (2) if the matrix has a multiple eigenvalue or complex eigenvalues, partial junk is returned. This is due to the eigenvalues having to be like |L1| > |L2| > ... > |Ln| for QR iteration to work properly.
